  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In most cases, a physics body should have a size and shape that closely approximates the visual representation of the corresponding node. For example, the rocket shown below has a narrow shape that is not well represented by either a circle or a rectangle. A convex polygon shape is chosen and fitted to match the sprite’s artwork."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2984898",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2984898",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Shape a Physics Body Using a Texture's Alpha Channel",
          "anchor": "3109113"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If you do not want to create your own shapes, you can use SpriteKit to create a shape for you based on the sprite’s texture."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "SKSpriteNode *sprite = [SKSpriteNode spriteNodeWithImageNamed:@\"Spaceship\"];",
            "sprite.physicsBody = [SKPhysicsBody bodyWithTexture:sprite.texture size:sprite.texture.size];"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3109115",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Choose a Simple Geometric Physics Body Shape",
          "anchor": "3109116"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When choosing a shape for your physics body, do not be overly precise. More complex shapes require more work to be properly simulated. For volume-based bodies, use the following guidelines:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A circle is the most efficient shape ("
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skphysicsbody/1520261-bodywithcircleofradius"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ")"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "A path-based polygon is the least efficient shape, and the computational work scales with the complexity of the polygon ("
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skphysicsbody/1520379-bodywithpolygonfrompath"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ")"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Use Edge-Based Physics Bodies Only When Needed",
          "anchor": "3109118"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "An edge-based body is more expensive to compute than a volume-based body. This is because the bodies it interacts with can potentially be on either side of an open edge or on the inside or outside of a closed shape. Use these guidelines:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "unorderedList",
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Lines and rectangles are the most efficient edge-based bodies ("
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skphysicsbody/1520401-bodywithedgefrompoint"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skphysicsbody/1520055-bodywithedgeloopfromrect"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ")"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Edge loops and edge chains are the most expensive edge-based bodies, and the computational work scales with the complexity of the path ("
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skphysicsbody/1519732-bodywithedgeloopfrompath"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": " and "
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "reference",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skphysicsbody/1519871-bodywithedgechainfrompath"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": ")."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
